From: Kairo POC <kairo-poc@local>
Date: Mon, 22 Jun 2026 10:00:00 -0700
Subject: [RFC/POC PATCH 11/9] mq-deadline: Kairo adaptive decode tail-latency controller

Subsystem touched:
- `block/mq-deadline.c`

Kairo concept:
- adaptive controller that adjusts Kairo scheduling policy based on observed
  decode tail latency
- three modes: OFF, OBSERVE (collect stats only), ADAPTIVE (adjust policy)
- tracks decode p99/p95/avg latency over a control window
- when decode p99 exceeds target: boost decode budget, throttle prefetch,
  increase write demotion pressure, preserve starvation escape
- when decode p99 is healthy: slowly relax decode budget, restore prefetch,
  allow prefill/write progress
- sysfs knobs: enable, mode, target p99, control window, observed budgets
- sysfs counters: updates, boost/relax events, prefetch throttles, write
  releases, insufficient sample events

COMPILE-RISK: LOW. All controller logic is self-contained in new static
helpers and sysfs boilerplate. It references existing Kairo enums and
deadline_data fields.

CONCEPTUAL-HOOK: The controller update point (dd_kairo_controller_update)
must be called periodically from the dispatch path or a timer. The exact
call site depends on how the scheduler sampling loop is structured.

Depends on:
- 0001: kairo_enable, struct kairo_hints, kairo_io_class
- 0009: sysfs show/store patterns, DD_RO_ATTR/DD_ATTR macros
- 0011: write deadline logic (preserved by controller)

